FFUF
Fast web fuzzer written in Go

Web Application
Description
FFUF (Fuzz Faster U Fool) is an extremely fast web fuzzer written in Go. It can fuzz various parts of HTTP requests including URLs, headers, and POST data.

Installation / Check
Check if installed:

which ffuf
Install command:

sudo apt install ffuf
Basic Syntax
ffuf -w <wordlist> -u <url/FUZZ>
Common Commands
Command	What it does	When to use	Risk
ffuf -w /usr/share/wordlists/dirb/common.txt -u http://target/FUZZ

Directory fuzzing	Fast directory discovery	
ffuf -w wordlist.txt -u http://target/FUZZ -e .php,.html

Fuzz with extensions	Finding files with specific extensions	
ffuf -w wordlist.txt -u http://target -H "Host: FUZZ.target.com"

Virtual host discovery	Finding subdomains on same IP	
ffuf -w wordlist.txt -u http://target/api?param=FUZZ

Parameter fuzzing	Testing API parameters	
ffuf -w wordlist.txt -u http://target/FUZZ -mc 200,301,302

Filter by status codes	Only show specific response codes	
Step-by-Step Guide
1
Prepare wordlist for fuzzing
2
Identify fuzz point in URL (use FUZZ keyword)
3
Run ffuf with appropriate options
4
Filter results by size, status, or words
5
Investigate interesting findings
Understanding the Output
Output shows: URL, Status code, Size, Words, Lines. Green results typically indicate found resources.

Important Warnings
•
Very fast tool - can overwhelm servers
•
Only fuzz authorized targets
•
Monitor for rate limiting
⚠️ Use Kali Linux tools only on systems you own or have written permission to test. Unauthorized hacking is illegal and can result in criminal charges.
